    "description": {
      "value": "<p>You focus Chakra into a mud river you've created with Doryuu Taiga no Jutsu and whose starting point is within range. A dragon-shaped head emerges from the mud and starts shooting mud balls at creatures caught inside the mud river. Each round, the dragon fires one mud ball per 3 levels, divided as you choose among creatures caught in the mud river (a creature can be targeted more than once). Each mud ball deals 1d6 earth damage, avoided with a Reflex save.<br><br>If you use a Fire technique which affects the dragon head, its projectiles will deal an additional 1d4 Fire damage for 1d4+1 rounds as it burns.<br><br>Ends once its duration expires, or if the Doryuu Taiga no Jutsu hosting it expires.</p>\n\n\n\n",
